question_What_type_of_author_does_this_w: What type of author does this work have?
hint_What_type_of_author_does_this_work_: For the purposes of this Calculator, - If a work is created at the initiative of a natural or legal person who edits it, publishes it and discloses it under his/her direction and name and where the personal contributions of the various authors who participated in its production are merged in the overall work for which they were conceived, so that it becomes impossible to attribute to each author a separate right in the work (collective work), the person who organizes and directs its creation should be deemed the author. - Where the work has been created by the indistinguishable and inseparable contributions of two or more persons (work of joint authorship), all contributors should be considered to be joint co- authors.
